Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Trim the @butternut squash{1}, halve lengthways, then scoop out the seeds
(peel first if you prefer). Cut into small 1cm chunks. Pop onto a
large #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.
Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf of the oven until golden and
tender, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

While the squash roasts, bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with
@salt{1/2%tsp} for the linguine.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced).
Cut the @Tenderstem® broccoli{80%g} into thirds. Peel and grate the
@garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Roughly tear the @Serrano ham{3%slice} into large pieces.

When your pan of water is boiling, add the @linguine{180%g} and bring back to
the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, reserve some of the pasta water (see pantry for amount),
reserve @reserved pasta water{125%ml}, then drain in a #colander{} and pop
back into the pan. Drizzle with oil and stir through to stop it sticking
together.

While your pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on
medium-high heat.

When hot, lay the Serrano in the pan and fry until crispy, ~{2-3%minutes}
each side, then transfer to a plate covered in kitchen paper and set aside.

Add a drizzle more oil to the pan, then add the
@diced British chicken breast{240%g}(diced). Stir-fry until golden brown
and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}. Set aside.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so
> there's no pink in the middle.

Put the frying pan back on medium high-heat then add the onion. Stir-fry
until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the broccoli and stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}. Add a splash of water and
cover with a #lid{} (or foil) and allow to cook until tender,
~{4-6%minutes} more. Season with salt and pepper.

Once the veg is tender, remove the lid, stir in the garlic and cook for
~{30%seconds}.

Pour the reserved pasta water and @chicken stock paste{10%g} into the pan,
then stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g} and Serrano ham. Bring to the boil,
then remove from the heat.

Add the cooked pasta, chicken and roasted butternut squash to the sauce.

Taste and add salt and pepper if needed. Add a splash of water if it's a
little thick.

Toss gently to coat in the sauce, then serve your linguine in large #bowls{}.

Enjoy!